<pre><code>class Program {     static void Method(out int i, out string s1, out string s2)     {         i = 44;         s1 = "I've been returned";         s2 = null;     }     static void Main()     {         int value;         string str1="fwer", str2;         Method(out value, out str1, out str2);         Console.WriteLine (str1);         Console.ReadKey();         // value is now 44         // str1 is now "I've been returned"         // str2 is (still) null;     } </code></pre>  <p>In the above I am initializing <code>str1</code> and sending the <code>str1</code> as out and changing the value in the caller method. as string is immutable. changing it should create a new string object. but how it's printing the value correctly in the calling method which changed in caller method.</p>  <p>thanks in advance.</p>